parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the biodegradable wiring harness can cause various engine problems, including acceleration issues, and potentially lead to a fire hazard, which can result in accidents or injuries.

The premature failure of the catalytic converters can cause the vehicle to run rough, especially during acceleration, and lead to increased emissions, which can harm the environment and public health.
The failure of the rear suspension can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: clunking or rattling noises from the rear suspension
difficulty steering or controlling the vehicle.
